rdensein, ihrer inneren Vielfalt und ihrer gesellschaftlichen, politischen und theologischen Relevanz zu erklären.  aThe second volume of History and Theology contains 23 articles by Rainer Albertz on the history of Israel, on literary and religious history, and on the anthropology and theology of the Old Testament. These articles demonstrate the Münster-based scholar’s project to explain the development, diversity, and societal, political, and theological relevance of Old Testament transmissions.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 4aAltes Testament. 4aGeschichte Israels. 4aHebräische Bibel. 4aLiteraturgeschichte. 4aTheologiegeschichte. 7aRELIGION / Biblical Criticism & Interpretation / Old Testament.2bisacsh  aBiblical theology.  aHebrew Bible.  aHistory of Israel.  aOld Testament.1 aEbach, Ruth, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aWöhrle, Jakob, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1z978311117578208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2023z9783111318820oZDB-23-DGF0 cEPUBz97831112029380 cprintz978311117981040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311120222840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783111202228423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783111202228/original  a978-3-11-117578-2  DG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1b2023  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGFb2023  aZDB-23-DGGb2023